        {
            "title": "Civil protection and climate vulnerability",
            "date": {
                "start": {
                    "month": null,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2009
                },
                "end": {
                    "month": null,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2011
                }
            },
            "description": "The Civil Protection and Climate Vulnerability (CIVILCLIM) project was an international research project carried out by a Dutch team represented by the researcher and her supervisor in close cooperation with researchers from Vestlandsforsking in Norway and Totalf\u00f6rsvarets forskningsinstitut (FOI) in Sweden. CIVILCLIM was funded by the Research Council of Norway.\n\nThe focus of the project was a comparative study into the adaptation strategies of the civil protection institutions in Norway, Sweden and the Netherlands. First, the national policy discourses on adaptation and civil protection in Norway, Sweden and the Netherlands were analyzed. Second, the civil protection system of a harbor area of significant national interest in the respective countries. As case study units, the civil protection systems of Bergen, Malm\u00f6 and Rotterdam were respectively selected.",
