        {
            "title": "Local climate preparedness in municipalities",
            "date": {
                "start": {
                    "month": null,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2010
                },
                "end": {
                    "month": null,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2011
                }
            },
            "description": "This regional project was funded by the Groot Salland water board under the INTERREG VIb project WAVE. WAVE combines the climate change preparations of six regional water authorities from the Netherlands, Germany, England, France and Belgium. The parties involved in WAVE have the responsibility to adapt water management to the changing climate. Impacts from climate change has to be taken into account in spatial development. An important question emerging from the field is how municipalities currently deal with climate change in their new neighborhood planning. \n\nThe Local climate preparedness in municipalities project focused on sustainable land use planning and climate proof areas, municipal disaster planning and climate change awareness. The project had a regional focus analyzing municipalities within the Dutch province of Overijssel and was carried out in close cooperation with representatives from the province and the Groot Salland and Regge & Dinkel Water Boards.",
