        {
            "title": "Analysing local climate vulnerability and local adaptation strategies",
            "date": {
                "start": {
                    "month": null,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2009
                },
                "end": {
                    "month": null,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2010
                }
            },
            "description": "This project was part of the research program Vulnerability, Adaptation and Mitigation (2004-2010) funded by the Netherlands Organisation for Scientific Research (NWO). The program focused on the social and behavioral aspects of climate change, particularly within and in cooperation between public administration, geography, environmental economics, social-cultural sciences, environmental law, psychology and other disciplines. The aim of our project was to get insights into the motivations for local climate adaptation strategies and in the barriers when implementing these policy plans. The project consisted of case study research into nine municipalities throughout the Netherlands.",
